// Man page for sniffer
manSniffer="SNIFFER(1)                         X Shell Manual                         SNIFFER(1)

<b>NAME</b>
    sniffer - Network packet capture and analysis
<b>SYNOPSIS</b>
    <b>sniffer</b> [save|deploy]
<b>DESCRIPTION</b>
    Network packet analyzer for monitoring and capturing traffic. Intercepts
    data packets traveling across network for analysis. Essential for
    credential harvesting, traffic analysis, and network reconnaissance.
    Use save to capture to file or deploy for standalone operation.
    Only one flag can be used at a time.
<b>OPTIONS</b>
    <b>sniffer</b>
    Launch integrated packet sniffer
    Real-time traffic monitoring

    <b>sniffer save</b>
    Capture packets and save encode.src
    Downloads encryption source to current directory

    <b>sniffer deploy</b>
    Deploy standalone sniffer
    Background packet capture
<b>EXAMPLE:</b>
    <color=#e4ff34># Real-Time Sniffing</color>
    <b>sniffer</b>
    Start live packet capture

    <color=#e4ff34># Save Encryption Source</color>
    <b>sniffer save</b>
    Capture and save encode.src to current directory

    <color=#e4ff34># Deployment</color>
    <b>sniffer deploy</b>
    Deploy persistent sniffer

    <color=#e4ff34># Credential Harvesting</color>
    <b>sniffer</b>
    Monitor for plaintext credentials

    <b>sniffer save</b>
    Save encode.src for offline analysis
<b>SEE ALSO</b>
    <b>scan</b>"